I am delighted to share one of the most memorable and transformative experiences of my life as a cadet in the National Cadet Corps (NCC). I attended the NCC ATC (Annual Training Camp) held in Tenali, which tested my discipline, endurance, and leadership skills. Through consistent hard work and dedication, I was selected for the prestigious Gun Firing Camp conducted in Guntur, where I had the opportunity to hold and operate a real rifle for the first time.

This experience has not only strengthened my confidence but also instilled in me a deeper respect for our armed forces and the spirit of teamwork.

